text: Kim Soo-mi (; born Kim Young-ok; September 3, 1949 â€“ October 25, 2024) was a South Korean actress. Kim became well known late in her career. She had a role in thr 2006 movie Barefoot Ki-bong. Her role in the 2011 movie Late Blossom also made her popular. She won Best Supporting Actress at the Blue Dragon Film Awards. Kim died at a hospital in Seoul, South Korea on October 25, 2024 from cardiac arrest caused by hyperglycemic shock, at the age of 75. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1949 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Deaths from cardiac arrest Category:South Korean movie actors Category:South Korean television actors Category:South Korean stage actors
